The Dockerfile does not meet the static criterion: it does not execute any build commands for the project. The Dockerfile only sets up the environment (installs dependencies, Swift toolchain, clones the repository) but does not include any RUN commands to actually build the SwiftNIO project. To fix this, add a build step such as 'RUN swift build' or 'RUN make' after setting the working directory to $SRC/swift-nio.